# 🏥 MediTriage — AI-Powered Symptom Severity Checker

> Built for CODE 1 Hackathon | Track: Rapid Response Racing | Organized by Collazon

---

## 📌 What is MediTriage?

MediTriage is an AI-powered web application that allows users to select their symptoms and instantly receive a predicted disease diagnosis along with recommended precautions. It is designed to improve healthcare accessibility and assist in early-stage triage.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Select multiple symptoms from a searchable list
- AI model predicts the most likely disease
- Displays disease description and recommended precautions
- Clean, dark-themed responsive UI
- Fast and lightweight — runs locally

---

## 🧠 How It Works

```
User selects symptoms
        ↓
Django backend receives form data
        ↓
Sklearn RandomForest model predicts disease
        ↓
App fetches description + precautions from CSV
        ↓
Result displayed on screen
```

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| ML Model | Python, Scikit-learn (RandomForestClassifier) |
| Backend | Django 6.0 |
| Frontend | HTML, CSS (custom dark theme) |
| Data | Kaggle Disease-Symptom Dataset |
| Model Export | Joblib |

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
meditriage/
├── core/                  # Django project settings
│   ├── settings.py
│   └── urls.py
├── predictor/             # Main app
│   ├── views.py           # ML model logic + routing
│   ├── urls.py
│   └── templates/
│       └── predictor/
│           └── index.html # Frontend UI
├── disease_model.pkl      # Trained ML model
├── symptoms_list.json     # All unique symptoms
├── dataset.csv            # Training data
├── symptom_Description.csv
├── symptom_precaution.csv
├── Symptom-severity.csv
└── manage.py
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup & Installation

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.x
- pip

### Steps

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/meditriage.git
cd meditriage

# 2. Install dependencies
pip install django scikit-learn joblib pandas

# 3. Run the server
python3 manage.py runserver

# 4. Open in browser
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

